The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for efficiently solving the planar range skyline reporting problem in external memory, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and database systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DB (Databases), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.AL (Algorithms).
